\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\rtlch\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\fs24\lang1033\loch\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 \tab \'93You\'92re a queeeeeeer\'94 Ryan sneered from behind us.  }
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\rtlch\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\fs24\lang1033\loch\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 \tab He was infinitely more clever than me.  Well, I don\'92t know if clever is the right word.  But he had special powers.  He could broadcast my weakest parts; put them on permanent, public display at the center of attention.  }
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\rtlch\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\fs24\lang1033\loch\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 \tab He was on the bus I rode to the middle school in the morning - the first time I got on he nearly lost it.}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\rtlch\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\fs24\lang1033\loch\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 \tab \'93Oh, not this kid.  Sit in the front.\'94 he commanded.  \'93I don\'92t want that guy anywhere near me.  He picks his nose and wipes it everywhere.\'94  I received a sustained look of horror from every passenger on the bus.  From then on, every morning when I reached
 the top of the stairs everyone would fill out their seats, set their backpacks beside them, until there was no place at all for me to sit.  }
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\rtlch\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\fs24\lang1033\loch\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 \tab \'93We can\'92t leave until everyone sits down!\'94  The bus driver would yell into that big rectangular rearview mirror.  \'93The bus isn\'92t even full!  Find a place to sit!\'94}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\rtlch\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\fs24\lang1033\loch\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 \tab The bus was full enough for me to get bogarted out of a seat.  Eventually I would sit down on the edge of some seat, the person occupying it reacting in bitter disgust, as if I were carrying with me a large, uncovered tupperware container full of human fe
ces.}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\rtlch\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\fs24\lang1033\loch\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 \tab I\'92m going to be perfectly honest with you, reader.  I feel like we\'92re establishing an intimate bond here, and I don\'92t intend to let any detail escape your grasp.  That\'92s why I have no qualms in telling you that in seventh grade, I did pick my nose.  Now, 
I could give you all sorts of legitimate excuses, like how my chronic allergies made this quite a beneficial activity, but the truth of the matter is that it was just a bad habit I had never gotten around to dropping.  Ryan had seen me in the act once.  I 
worked so diligently to conceal it, but this kid was a bloodhound for embarrassment.  I hadn\'92t stood a chance.  }
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\rtlch\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\fs24\lang1033\loch\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 \tab He turned the crowd against me.}
