\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\rtlch\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\fs24\lang1033\loch\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 \tab The big concrete room was silent without a single reverberated echo.  It was Thursday.  My hands began to shake a little, fingers woven into the chicken wire bars, as I thought about when the morning janitor would come in, if someone would pass through th
at night, or - }
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\rtlch\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\fs24\lang1033\loch\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 \tab I heard voices!  Coming my way!  Ian and Skyler rounded the hallway between the locker room and the bathroom and I caught a fleeting glimpse of them - shirts slung over their shoulders as they began to leave the school.  }
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\rtlch\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\fs24\lang1033\loch\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 \tab \'93HEY!\'94 I yelled, though my voice was trying against my will to be small and embarrassed.}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\rtlch\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\fs24\lang1033\loch\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 \tab They turned and scanned the locker room at eye level, confused, so I yelled some more.}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\rtlch\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\fs24\lang1033\loch\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 \tab \'93Oh shit dude.\'94  Skyler dropped down to where I sat, caged.  \'93What\'92s your combination?\'94}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\rtlch\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\fs24\lang1033\loch\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 \tab \'9336,\'94  I chocked out, \'9324 . . . 57.\'94  I swear to god, that\'92s the exact combination.  Some events brand themselves permanently into your mind, and this was one of them.  }
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\sl480\slmult1\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\ql\rtlch\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\fs24\lang1033\loch\fs24\lang1033{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f1\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0{\rtlch\ltrch\hich\f2\loch\f2 \tab \'93You are so lucky,\'94 Skyler explained frantically, \'93Me and Ian were staying late to rub cold water on our nipples to make them hard for when we walked out }}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f1\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0{\rtlch\ltrch\hich\f2\i\loch\f2\i or we never would have seen you.}{\rtlch\ltrch\hich\f2\loch\f2 \'94}}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\sl480\slmult1\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\ql\rtlch\af2\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af2\langfe255\hich\f2\fs24\lang1033\loch\f2\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 \tab I tumbled out of the locker onto the brushed concrete floor.  Uninjured, physically.  Not left to starve.  }
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\sl480\slmult1\ql\rtlch\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f2\fs24\lang1033\loch\f2\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 \tab And since that day, I have never once stepped into a locker.}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\rtlch\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\fs24\lang1033\loch\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 \tab Like I said about going back and changing things - some things are going to happen, at some point or another, regardless of what you do.  They are the lessons you cannot skip, only delay.  If not then, I would have eventually realized that my body was the
 perfect shape for squeezing into lockers.  I was skinny all through high school; if I would have pulled that shit then, the door would have locked automatically, and there\'92d have been no air holes.  Probably no sympathetic teammates either.  This is why y
ou do not question the big things, no matter how awful they are.}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\rtlch\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\fs24\lang1033\loch\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 \tab When I arrived home that night, I met Emily online.}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\rtlch\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\fs24\lang1033\loch\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 \tab \'93How was you day?\'94 she asked me.  }
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\rtlch\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\fs24\lang1033\loch\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 \tab \'93Fine :)\'94 I replied.  Right then it was.  If you would have asked Emily you\'92d have received a completely different story of that year, one in which Ryan\'92s shenanigans left my mind moments after they happened, that did not bother all that much to begin wit
h.  I was not upset.  I was not bubbling inside with inarticulate frustration, building pressure like a two liter of mountain dew rattling around in the trunk of a Chevy Cavalier, turning and skidding around blind corners.  Slide-bam, sliiiide-bam.  Every 
hit compromised my grey wool interior.  }
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\rtlch\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\fs24\lang1033\loch\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 \tab In the week before the big spring dance I was walking with Emily after science class, where we would part ways and I would head on to gym.  I was turned back talking to her when Ryan pulled a cannonball shove.  How this works is one person (the cannonball
) is pushed, comically, by the other (the cannon) in a way that appears as though they are obliviously lost in their own horseplay.  But the intent is for the cannonball to ram themselves into an opposing party as hard as possible in a way that looks like 
an accident.  Ryan collided into me at full force, smashing me into a wall.  My hip burnt with an indecipherable pain as it attempted to reconcile the metal handrail that had suddenly introduced itself to my side.  I fell to my knees as Ryan yelled \'93Sorry!
\'94 and scampered his way down the hall.}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\rtlch\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\fs24\lang1033\loch\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 \tab Emily knelt to see if I was ok.  I really was not.  My side hurt bad, there was that, but I was literally exploding inside, in tiny adrenal fireworks that battered the inside of my organs.}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\rtlch\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\fs24\lang1033\loch\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 \tab \'93I hate him soooo much,\'94 I attempted to explain.  Emily was trying to help me to my feet and I was trying to keep her from doing so.  And then I was crying.  I could feel it, that burning eruption that gives not alternative but complete, fully visible cat
harsis.}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\rtlch\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\fs24\lang1033\loch\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 \tab \'93Are you ok?\'94 Emily asked, the most sincere look of concern on her scared, unaware little face.  \'93Do you - do you need a nurse?\'94}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\rtlch\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\fs24\lang1033\loch\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 \tab I pushed away from her and ran haphazardly down the hall, away from the people that had begun to gather and stare.  }
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\rtlch\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\fs24\lang1033\loch\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 \tab I stopped in a back hallway to sob behind a rolled up wrestling mat.  }
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\rtlch\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\fs24\lang1033\loch\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 \tab His last named rhymed with sperm.  How had no one ever pointed that out?  Why couldn\'92t I think of that when he looked me in the eye and called me a faggot?  He was a fucking ginger for chrissake, why the fuck was I the one taking the beating?  I\'92ll tell y
ou why.  It\'92s because he was stronger, in some indefinable way.  He was superlative.  }
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\rtlch\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\fs24\lang1033\loch\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 \tab Sometimes you can convince yourself that if you just push back a little harder, the outside forces holding you down will admit defeat, and life will crack open the frothy cask of earthly spoils you so rightly deserve.  You really do deserve them, if you\'92v
e been any kind of decent person.  I was not all that bad.  I could see, however obscured, a path for me that lead to a completely different place.  I had a girlfriend and a track sweatshirt.  I had a bruise the size of a plum on my hip bone but you couldn
\'92t see it underneath said sweatshirt.  I didn\'92t even remove it for the dance that friday, which was a bad choice, considering the oven our gym became when Deborah Cox\'92s slowjam hit \'93Nobody\'92s Supposed to be Here\'94 began to mute snare its way around the dance
 floor.  Emily was meeting me there.  I stood outside with Steven, bobbing my head anxiously to a silent rhythm in my mind.  }
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\rtlch\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\fs24\lang1033\loch\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 \tab \'93Girlfriends.\'94 I said.  \'93We\'92re going to dance with our girlfriends.\'94}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\rtlch\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\fs24\lang1033\loch\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 \tab \'93Yes we are.\'94 Steven replied, completely cool, though I knew he felt the excitement just the same as me.  He always handled these situation so much better than me.}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\rtlch\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\fs24\lang1033\loch\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 \tab Inside we were able to find Anna and Emily, and we all walked together into the gym.  There we recklessly oscillated to Jennifer Lopez and Brittney Spears, the same repetitive loop of tiny hihats and digital bass thumps that matched the frequency in our t
iny, underdeveloped brains.}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\rtlch\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\fs24\lang1033\loch\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 \tab I heard the first slow downbeat.  I didn\'92t have to wait at all.  I turned to Emily.  }
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\rtlch\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\fs24\lang1033\loch\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 \tab \'93Would you like to dance?\'94 I asked in my most charming tone.  It was probably not all that charming.  }
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\rtlch\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\fs24\lang1033\loch\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 \tab \'93S-sure\'94 she said, placing her arms on my shoulder.  I placed my hands lightly upon her hips.}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\rtlch\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\fs24\lang1033\loch\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 \tab She twitched a little bit, removed my hands from her waist, and placed them upon her shoulders.}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\rtlch\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\fs24\lang1033\loch\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 \tab I moved my hands back to her hips - Emily clearly did not know how we were to dance.}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\rtlch\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\fs24\lang1033\loch\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 \tab \'93N-no,\'94 she stuttered, \'93I don\'92t actually want to . . .\'94}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\rtlch\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\fs24\lang1033\loch\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 \tab \'93To what?\'94 I asked.  I was not gong to put my hands on her shoulders.  We looked like two zombies slowly trying to strangle each other.  People were starring.}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\rtlch\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\fs24\lang1033\loch\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 \tab \'93I know, but -\'94 she looked me right in the eyes.  \'93I don\'92t want to.\'94}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\sl480\slmult1\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\ql\rtlch\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\fs24\lang1033\loch\fs24\lang1033{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f1\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0{\rtlch\ltrch\hich\f2\loch\f2 \tab \'93But }}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f1\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0{\rtlch\ltrch\hich\f2\i\loch\f2\i that\'92s}{\rtlch\ltrch\hich\f2\loch\f2  how you }{\rtlch\ltrch\hich\f2\i\loch\f2\i dance.}{\rtlch\ltrch\hich\f2\loch\f2 \'94  I was not understanding her reasoning at all.  Our friends and teachers were all there, our enemies, the whole school.  We couldn\'92t dance like morons.}}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\sl480\slmult1\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\ql\rtlch\af2\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af2\langfe255\hich\f2\fs24\lang1033\loch\f2\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 \tab I placed my hands on her hips one more time.  Emily looked at me and began to sob.  Then she began to full on cry.  She hid her face in her hands and just stood there, did not walk to the bathroom, did not try to find Anna, she just stood there helpless a
nd still, trying to hide behind her wet fingers.  To this day, that\'92s the only time I\'92ve ever caused a girl to cry right there in front of me.}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\sl480\slmult1\ql\rtlch\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f2\fs24\lang1033\loch\f2\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 \tab So here the final thing, about the going back and changing things.  Making Emily cry was a big thing, an important thing, a thing that would have happened sometime if not then.  But it is impossible for me to say that I am glad that it happened, that I wo
uldn\'92t change it if I could go back.  Its vapor has hung on for years, imbuing into me a sort of trepidation and fear that still gets me ridiculed by my male cohorts.  To this day, the slightest hint of a \'91no\'92 stops me dead in my tracks - I feel that awkwa
rd humidity of the dance floor and see the tiny fragments of eye between her soft pink hands, and I stop.  This past friday night I brought home with me this beautiful drunken girl I had been chasing around for weeks, but when we got to my apartment we jus
t sat on my couch and I read her this story.  I know, I know.  I was making us more alcoholic drinks when she found a rough draft of it on my coffee table, restlessly fidgeting through my things, her fear and uneasiness as clear as the heavily creased fold
s she was making into the first couple of pages.  I put our drinks back and brought out a couple of waters.  As I began to recite it out loud, I felt the tension she had possessed relax and I remembered the way Emily had sounded when I had called her the d
ay after that dance, to tell her that she was off the hook, that she could take it easy now.  That was the first time I knew I was doing a right thing, and in it was the only lesson I can unearth from all of it.  This one, dumb little thing I have to offer
.}
